text: To all of you people who are hating on this movie before it even hits theaters I challenge to not go and see it. If you say that this movie is a joke, then don't give the makers your money when it comes out. I don't care if Agent 47 is a "silent" killer. You all seem to forget that he was made to be an assassin, not just a sniper. In the real world he could never be as "silent" as he is in games because in the games silencers seem to mask all noise, whereas in real life a silencer only reduces the range of the gunshot to a few hundred yards. So all of you just shut up and accept that this actually looks like a really cool movie.

text: I just got back from watching Hitman: Agent 47. After reading the critical reviews the film had received, I was skeptical. But after viewing this film in all its glory at my local cinema...Never have I had so little faith in critics. So much faith in humanity. Hitman is a beautiful story about the triumph of the will with dialogue so realistic and authentic, it makes Quentin Tarantino look like a retarded chimpanzee with a heroin addiction. Rupert Friend gives such a layered, emotional and deep performance that it rivals Benicio Del Toro in Traffic. All of the critics who have seen this movie burn with a raging jealousy towards the films director, the multitalented editing and storytelling genius that is Aleksander Bach. I pity them and hope that they can someday find the true depth and meaning I have found in this cinematic gift from the Heavens....      Just kidding, this film gave me cancer.

text: At least cast someone who looks or sounds like 47. Why didn't they just make him Agent [some other number], instead? Just have 47 do a cameo appearance.  The movie title is "The Agent"  The story follows agent 56, a bioengineered supersoldier-hitman just like 47. The movie follows him trying to solve some conspiracy or whatever, figuring out more and more about his past or "who's behind all this" and stuff, you know, the classic stuff. But the real twist and fan surprise comes at the end.  So, this Agent 56 finishes his assignment by putting a bullet into a drug kingpin's head. He has figured everything out. The kingpin gave him the last piece of the grand puzzle. He turns around to exit through the door of the drug lord's office . But as soon as he turns around, he gets shot in the head and he collapses. The camera zooms in out through the window behind him to one of the cars on a rundown ferris wheel. There he is, 47. He reloads his bolt action after uttering one phrase: "so, unprofessional." Cut to the credits. BAM.
